1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,169
<i>It's sad, isn't it?</i>
<i>The same thing happened</i>

2
00:00:03,253 --> 00:00:05,005
<i>with Louisa and Kyle.</i>

3
00:00:05,088 --> 00:00:06,631
<i>They painted Louisa as the bad guy</i>

4
00:00:06,715 --> 00:00:09,467
<i>when they didn't even</i>
<i>know the whole story yet.</i>

5
00:00:11,469 --> 00:00:13,888
<i>Don't they really</i>
<i>believe that Edong is still alive?</i>

6
00:00:13,972 --> 00:00:15,890
<i>We can spread out a picture of Edong</i>

7
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,934
<i>to get information about his whereabouts.</i>

8
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,602
<i>Edong doesn't have a scar on his back.</i>

9
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:22,355
<i>And now, it is clear</i>
<i>that Angelo had nothing to do with it.</i>

10
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:23,857
<i>Edong broke into our house.</i>

11
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,191
<i>He took our family picture.</i>

12
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:27,360
<i>He sent it along with</i>
<i>the message he sent to Beth.</i>

13
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:28,695
<i>He threatened my family.</i>

14
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,864
<i>We need to catch</i>
<i>that bastard as soon as possible.</i>

15
00:00:30,947 --> 00:00:34,451
<i>Alice? Do you remember</i>
<i>your old schoolmate, Kyle?</i>

16
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,578
<i>He and Louisa had a fight before.</i>

17
00:00:36,661 --> 00:00:39,372
<i>I only knew because</i>
<i>his parents went to my church.</i>

18
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:41,207
<i>He returned to Amurao.</i>

19
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:43,334
<i>If he came back after two years,</i>

20
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:46,504
<i>then he was here in</i>
<i>Amurao when Louisa died?</i>

21
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>Rapist!</i>

22
00:00:53,511 --> 00:00:54,596
<i>What did you just say?</i>

23
00:00:57,974 --> 00:00:58,975
<i>You're a rapist!</i>

24
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,101
<i>Shut up!</i>

25
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:03,188
<i>- Rapist!</i>
- [both grunting angrily]

26
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:05,273
<i>- Get off of me!</i>
<i>- You liked it!</i>

27
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,400
<i>Even if you don't say it,</i>

28
00:01:07,484 --> 00:01:08,985
<i>I know you meant yes!</i>

29
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:17,869
[theme music playing]

30
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:32,360
- [morose music playing]
- [waves crashing]

31
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:49,711
[young Lucas] <i>Me too! See?</i>

32
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,546
[young Edong] <i>Bro, just use your brain.</i>

33
00:02:51,629 --> 00:02:53,840
<i>- That's what you're good at.</i>
- [Dolores chuckles]

34
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:55,133
[young Lucas] <i>What are you talking about?</i>

35
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:57,343
- [Dolores] <i>Hey, you two!</i>
- [all chuckle]

36
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,512
[young Lucas]<i> What now? Come on!</i>

37
00:03:00,096 --> 00:03:02,473
<i>- Show me what you got!</i>
- [Dolores]<i> Oh, you two!</i>

38
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:03,600
[young Lucas] <i>What now?</i>

39
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:07,478
[faint laughter]

40
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:16,404
[music fades]

41
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:18,239
Does anyone still live here?

42
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:22,785
[waves crashing]

43
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:26,706
My aunt took over the house
when Edong went to prison,

44
00:03:27,707 --> 00:03:29,792
they left a few years later.

45
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:34,797
A storm damaged it.
It hasn't been fixed since.

46
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:40,762
You know what,
I could just blame you and your friends.

47
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:44,724
And also Celestino.

48
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:49,229
With everything that has happened.

49
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:52,982
But I won't.

50
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:58,988
If it weren't for my father,
none of this would have happened.

51
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:02,158
[waves continue crashing]

52
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,202
My father killed my mother.

53
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,919
That's when my
brother started to fall apart.

54
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:21,844
Do you want me to check it for you?

55
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:25,390
I'll come with you.

56
00:04:31,854 --> 00:04:33,690
- [phone ringing in distance]
- Uh…

57
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:36,901
you and Erica…

58
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:39,237
you guys are pretty close, huh?

59
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:42,365
Are you guys together?

60
00:04:42,782 --> 00:04:47,704
[playful music playing]

61
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,330
Hmm.

62
00:04:50,039 --> 00:04:51,791
It's complicated.

63
00:04:53,209 --> 00:04:54,377
Hold on,

64
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:57,338
It's complicated
with her and Lucas, too, right?

65
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:02,176
Are these the relationships
Erica wants to be in?

66
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:11,978
- [melancholic music playing]
- [wind rustling]

67
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:34,792
[melancholic music continues]

68
00:05:40,214 --> 00:05:41,758
[music fades]

69
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,217
Man, any updates?

70
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:45,887
Luckily, there are still
some left in the records.

71
00:05:47,346 --> 00:05:48,431
Here.

72
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,767
It says here in the report,

73
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:53,227
that four people died in the fire.

74
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,229
Five people were reported injured.

75
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,398
That's it.

76
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,317
[Ryan sighs exasperatedly]

77
00:06:00,401 --> 00:06:02,320
[whispers] I'll text you the names.

78
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:06,991
Bro, this stays between us, alright?

79
00:06:07,575 --> 00:06:09,035
If it weren't because you're my friend…

80
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:11,913
Oh, please.
We'll find out about what's written there.

81
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,998
You just made it easier for us.

82
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,251
But are you really
sure that Edong is still alive?

83
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:20,338
[sighs heavily] We are, man.

84
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,256
That's why I told you right away.

85
00:06:23,382 --> 00:06:25,468
Your organization
doesn't want to believe it.

86
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:27,136
That's why you're
being called incompetent.

87
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:28,387
You guys are falling behind.

88
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:30,098
Really now, man?

89
00:06:30,515 --> 00:06:32,225
I'm helping you, aren't I?

90
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:34,060
Man, I didn't say you're one of them.

91
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:36,229
You are an exception.

92
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:38,189
And I believe that one day,

93
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:41,109
you will be the head of the police force.

94
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:42,110
[snickers]

95
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:43,945
- Thank you.
- Go now.

96
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,573
- [Lucas sighs heavily]
- [car door closes]

97
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:50,326
[car door closes]

98
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,787
Your investigator seems to be right.

99
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:54,956
No one lives here anymore.

100
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:58,376
I made Yuri check
everywhere Edong could be hiding.

101
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:03,005
Even here. Though I had a strong feeling

102
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:05,216
he won't go come here.

103
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:09,971
After everything
that happened in that house,

104
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:12,265
I'm sure my brother
would never go back there.

105
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:19,897
Thank you.

106
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:21,607
For what?

107
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:24,277
[sympathetic music playing]

108
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,653
For coming here.

109
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,031
[Erica sighs heavily]

110
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,160
I know this is hard for you.

111
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:36,372
To look for your brother
with someone you don't like.

112
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:39,000
So…

113
00:07:40,084 --> 00:07:41,169
thank you.

114
00:07:56,476 --> 00:08:01,397
[sympathetic music continues]

115
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:02,732
I should hate you.

116
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:10,198
I have a lot of reasons to feel that way.

117
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:17,914
But with everything that has happened…

118
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:22,418
I can't even to hate you.

119
00:08:25,922 --> 00:08:31,385
[sympathetic music continues]

120
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:39,769
[phone ringing]

121
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:49,987
Alice, what's the matter?

122
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:52,949
It's Kyle.

123
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:54,534
Kyle?

124
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:56,661
Kyle Sebastian?

125
00:08:57,078 --> 00:08:58,412
Yes, Erica.

126
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:00,873
He was here…

127
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:02,416
in Amurao

128
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,752
the night that Louisa was killed.

129
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:08,756
[suspenseful music playing]

130
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,385
What-- No, he was in the US at the time.

131
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:14,262
Not at that time.

132
00:09:15,012 --> 00:09:16,556
Uncle Edward said

133
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,599
he and his family were here.

134
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,185
But they didn't tell anyone.

135
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:25,898
He had a good reason to kill Louisa.

136
00:09:26,482 --> 00:09:27,483
Remember?

137
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:31,112
[suspenseful music continues, fades]

138
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:37,410
- [morose music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

139
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:43,958
- [man]<i> Hit him!</i>
- [young Louisa]<i> Lester!</i>

140
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,043
- [kick lands]
<i>- Come on!</i>

141
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:47,503
[young Louisa]<i> Lester!</i>

142
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:49,422
- [blows landing]
- [men cheering]

143
00:09:49,505 --> 00:09:52,300
<i>- Lester! Lester, stop it!</i>
- [blows landing]

144
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:53,342
<i>- Aah!</i>
- [body thuds]

145
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:55,052
<i>- Louisa!</i>
- [men cheering] <i>Hey!</i>

146
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,804
- [man] <i>Hit him!</i>
- [blows landing]

147
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:58,055
<i>Lester!</i>

148
00:09:58,139 --> 00:09:59,765
<i>Lester, stop it! Please!</i>

149
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,977
<i>Hey! I think</i>
<i>your brother is going crazy, Louisa.</i>

150
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,061
<i>Put him on a leash!</i>

151
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:08,941
[morose music continues]

152
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,116
- [thwacks]
- [bag thuds]

153
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:19,118
[music fades]

154
00:10:19,201 --> 00:10:20,119
<i>Hey!</i>

155
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:21,495
<i>Are you okay?</i>

156
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:26,751
[intriguing music playing]

157
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:28,210
<i>Let me.</i>

158
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,140
<i>Ignore them.</i>

159
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:45,311
<i>Thanks.</i>

160
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:49,106
<i>Uh, if you're free later…</i>

161
00:10:49,607 --> 00:10:51,275
<i>we hang out at the boardwalk.</i>

162
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:52,902
<i>Come by.</i>

163
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:05,665
[intriguing music continues]

164
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:16,675
[indistinct chatter]

165
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,102
<i>- Your girl is here.</i>
- [Kyle chuckles]

166
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:27,353
<i>- I'll get going.</i>
<i>- Alright. See you.</i>

167
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:28,521
<i>Sure, sure.</i>

168
00:11:32,274 --> 00:11:33,818
<i>I thought you weren't coming.</i>

169
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:38,030
[intriguing music continues]

170
00:11:42,868 --> 00:11:44,995
[young Kyle]
<i>I thought your parents were dead.</i>

171
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:46,580
- [music fades]
- [Louisa chuckles]

172
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:49,625
<i>Looks like there's one person</i>
<i>in Amurao who doesn't know yet.</i>

173
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:51,377
[both chuckles softly]

174
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:52,378
<i>Okay.</i>

175
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:55,881
<i>My mom and dad both worked abroad.</i>

176
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:58,467
<i>My mom…</i>

177
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:00,803
<i>- cheated.</i>
<i>- Hm.</i>

178
00:12:01,929 --> 00:12:03,931
<i>So my father went and got a new wife.</i>

179
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:06,851
[Kyle sighs]

180
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:07,935
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

181
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:10,646
<i>Is my family's story too sad?</i>

182
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:11,981
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

183
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:13,232
<i>Don't apologize.</i>

184
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:15,734
<i>You need someone to talk to, right?</i>

185
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:17,486
<i>That's what I'm here for.</i>

186
00:12:21,282 --> 00:12:25,953
[foreboding music playing]

187
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:27,580
[young Kyle] <i>Louisa, let's go here.</i>

188
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,835
<i>Wow. Does your family own this?</i>

189
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:34,378
[water trickling]

190
00:12:34,462 --> 00:12:35,546
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

191
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:37,256
<i>Come on.</i>

192
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:41,802
[young Kyle grunts]

193
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:43,637
<i>You got it?</i>

194
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,225
[both chuckle]

195
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:49,268
<i>- I got it.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

196
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:51,770
<i>- Oh!</i>
<i>- Hey!</i>

197
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:53,772
<i>You okay?</i>

198
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:55,524
<i>Uh…</i> [chuckles]

199
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:57,610
<i>- I'm okay.</i>
- [young Kyle chuckles]

200
00:12:57,693 --> 00:12:58,652
<i>Be careful.</i>

201
00:12:59,403 --> 00:13:00,321
<i>Oh!</i>

202
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:03,115
<i>I got you. Don't worry.</i>

203
00:13:03,532 --> 00:13:04,783
<i>- I'm okay.</i>
- [young Kyle chuckles]

204
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:07,620
<i>Sit down.</i>

205
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:09,955
[young Kyle chuckles]

206
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,209
<i>Beer?</i>

207
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:15,794
[Louisa chuckles softly]

208
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:16,962
<i>- I don't drink.</i>
<i>- Tsk.</i>

209
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:18,088
<i>I don't want to be like my brothers--</i>

210
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,007
<i>Louisa, just this once.</i>

211
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,676
- [can clicks open]
- [young Kyle grunts softly]

212
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:23,886
<i>Here.</i>

213
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:28,182
[young Kyle scoffs]

214
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:29,808
[uneasy music playing]

215
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:31,393
[can hisses, clicks]

216
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,686
[young Kyle grunts]

217
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:35,272
[chuckles softly]

218
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,443
<i>- Ugh!</i>
- [young Kyle laughs]

219
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:42,071
<i>It'll taste better later.</i>

220
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:44,490
[young Kyle chuckles]

221
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:51,372
[music becomes gentle]

222
00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:57,503
<i>You know, everyone</i>
<i>at school thinks I'm a loser.</i>

223
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,340
<i>But not you.</i>

224
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:04,885
<i>So you think I'm special?</i>

225
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,389
<i>Because for me, Louisa…</i>

226
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:11,684
<i>I think you're special.</i>

227
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:15,020
<i>And I want to get to know you more.</i>

228
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:22,486
[stirring music playing]

229
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:31,787
[crickets chirping]

230
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:33,873
[Louisa giggles]

231
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,254
[music softens]

232
00:14:40,337 --> 00:14:41,964
<i>Tsk.</i> [inhales]

233
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:45,843
[Louisa gasps]

234
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:49,597
<i>Is Amurao still in the Philippines?</i>

235
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:52,057
[chuckles]

236
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:56,353
<i>Why are there two moons?</i>

237
00:14:58,772 --> 00:14:59,857
[Louisa laughs]

238
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:03,611
[exhales loudly]

239
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:09,283
[unsettling music playing]

240
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:17,207
<i>Wait-- What time is it?</i>

241
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,543
<i>I need to go home.</i>

242
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:22,087
<i>Not yet, Louisa.</i>

243
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:24,006
<i>Louisa, please stay.</i>

244
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:27,968
<i>- Kyle, I need to go home.</i>
<i>- Please, come on, please.</i>

245
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:30,679
<i>Louisa, please.</i>

246
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:31,764
<i>Let's stay here.</i>

247
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:34,558
